    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A \"deliberate attempt to simulate a real-world scenario\" is a massive reach for just 50 email addresses, isn't it? If we tell them we were running a simulation but didn't notify users or follow standard testing protocols, we might actually look worse. Are you sure we shouldn't just stick to the truth and say it was a minor technical glitch? It might be safer for the brand in the long run.",
